The paper deals with learning properties of accelerated gradient descent methods for linear least-squares in Hilbert spaces. This topic falls under the broad area of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of optimization for machine learning. The paper uses techniques from numerical analysis, optimization, and probability theory. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
